backgroundInformationList.description: Amendment of Designating By-law - 292 Main Street

contact.contactName: Toronto and East York Community Council

noticeDescription: Take notice that the Council of the City of Toronto has passed By-law 1146-2020 to amend By-law 935-2020 to designate 292 Main Street (Beaches-East York, Ward 19) as being of cultural heritage value or interest.

otherReferenceList.description: 2020.TE16.17 - Inclusion on the City of Toronto's Heritage Register, Intention to Designate under Part IV, Section 29 of the Ontario Heritage Act, Alterations to a Heritage Property and Authority to Enter into a Heritage Easement Agreement - 292 Main Street
By-Law 1146-2020 - To amend By-law 935-2020, being a by-law to designate the property at 292 Main Street as being of cultural heritage value or interest, to correct a technical error.

signedBy: John D. Elvidge, Interim City Clerk
subheading: In the Matter of the Ontario Heritage Act R.S.O. 1990 Chapter 0.18 and 292 Main Street City of Toronto, Province of Ontario
title: Amendment of Designating By-law - 292 Main Street
topics: Heritage > Amendment to the designation of a heritage property
